summary:
I am molecular biologist specialized in medical and food biochemistry with seven years of research and academic experience gained during work at polish scientific institutions (University of Warmia and Mazury and Polish Academy of Science) and collaboration with European institutions due to participation in EU-funded project (EuroPrevall). 

I have a strong background in the field of proteomics, food and medical biochemistry, immunology and cell biology. The main areas of my interests are:
•	Cell biology – the mechanisms of inflammation and allergy in human
•	Maillard reaction in food systems 
•	Protein chemistry and biochemistry 

During my PhD studies I studied the influence of food processing and Maillard reaction in food systems on physiochemical and biological properties of food proteins. I extended my research profile on immunogenicity and allergenicity of food proteins during collaboration with Cell Biology and Immunology Group at WU and realisation of individual research project funded by Polish Ministry of Science and Higher Education. After my PhD I continued my research career as post-doc at University of Warmia and Mazury in Olsztyn. Since October 2012 I'm employed on the position of post-doc researcher at Wageningen University where I realise the research project on influence of food processing on immunomodulatory and pro-inflammatory properties of food compounds.

Specialties: • Proteomics: protein extraction end purification, UV-Vis, fluorescence, DLS, chromatography - SPE, SEC, HPLC, FPLC; in vitro gastric hydrolysis, SDS-PAGE  1D&2D; 
• Immunology: ELISA, western-blot, antibodies production, vaccine preparation, immunization, purification of antibodies
• Cell culture: Caco-2, PBMCs, THP-1, HepG2  knowledge of flow cytometry
• Genetics: DNA/RNA isolation, PCR, gene expression analysis by QR-PCR
